ZH: 我们的孩子将在下个月接受洗礼。
EN: Our child will be baptized next month.

ZH: 洗礼是基督教中的一个重要仪式。
EN: Baptism is an important ceremony in Christianity.

ZH: 这个教堂每年都会举行洗礼仪式。
EN: This church holds baptism ceremonies every year.

ZH: 在洗礼仪式上，孩子们将被赐予新名字。
EN: During the baptism ceremony, children are given a new name.

ZH: 洗礼代表着信徒对宗教的承诺。
EN: Baptism symbolizes a believer's commitment to their faith.

ZH: 我们需要提前预约孩子的洗礼仪式。
EN: We need to make an appointment for our child's baptism ceremony.

ZH: 洗礼水象征着信徒的洗净和重生。
EN: Baptismal water symbolizes the cleansing and rebirth of a believer.

ZH: 教堂内的祭坛是洗礼仪式的中心。
EN: The altar in the church is the center of the baptism ceremony.

ZH: 他刚刚被洗礼，已经成为了一名基督徒。
EN: He has just been baptized and has become a Christian.

ZH: 洗礼是进入教会的第一步。
EN: Baptism is the first step to entering the church.

ZH: 洗礼有很多不同的形式和仪式。
EN: Baptism has many different forms and ceremonies.

ZH: 在洗礼仪式上，孩子们通常会穿白色的礼服。
EN: Children usually wear white robes during the baptism ceremony.

ZH: 我们为了庆祝洗礼，举办了一个派对。
EN: We held a party to celebrate the baptism.

ZH: 家庭成员和朋友会在洗礼仪式上出席。
EN: Family members and friends will attend the baptism ceremony.

ZH: 这个教堂的洗礼仪式非常庄严肃穆。
EN: The baptism ceremony at this church is very solemn.

ZH: 他已经决定在洗礼仪式上当一名教父。
EN: He has decided to be a godfather at the baptism ceremony.

ZH: 洗礼是让信徒获得神的祝福和保护。
EN: Baptism is a way for believers to receive God's blessing and protection.

ZH: 受洗礼是我一生中最重要的时刻之一。
EN: Being baptized was one of the most important moments in my life.

ZH: 孩子们通常在出生后不久接受洗礼。
EN: Children usually receive baptism shortly after birth.

ZH: 洗礼是信仰的象征和见证。
EN: Baptism is a symbol and testimony of faith.
